The facilities of university libraries were expanded; Novorossiysk University was founded (1864); issued a special charter for Dorpat University.A. V. Golovnin raised the importance of the Ministry of Public Education, which before him was considered one of the secondary ones; he almost doubled his budget, while cutting back on unproductive expenditures; destroyed the office of the minister and concentrated the entire administrative part in the reorganized department of public education. Golovnin transformed the main board of schools into the Council of Ministers. A. Tolstoy, "placed classical education as the basis of proper scientific university education."